modules.description: Provides functions for reading from and writing to C-like structures using Bigarray, enabling direct memory manipulation. Works with byte sequences and structured data layouts represented as arrays. Used to parse and generate binary data formats such as network packets or file headers.

Provides functions to create Cstruct buffers from Unix file descriptors, enabling direct memory-mapped access to file contents. Operates on Cstruct.t and Unix.file_descr types, allowing low-level I/O operations. Used for efficiently reading and writing files without explicit buffer copying.
